$\frac{1}{n}H(\textsf{L})\leq R+\epsilon$ for all sufficiently large $n$. We denote the infimum among all achievable ${\text{CI}}_W$ (resp.\ ${\text{CI}}$) rates by ${\text{CI}}_W(X_{\mathcal{M}})$ (resp. \ ${\text{CI}}(X_{\mathcal{M}})$).
